Did a rescue run today for Sebastian, Chicken Little and Gizmo. All three need fosters ASAP through @pacificpupsrescue. Sebastian is 8 months old and does well with other dogs. He is very shy but a gentle soul. Chicken Little is 3 years old and does well with others too. He is a little underweight so he’ll be living the dream hitting the buffet hard. Lastly, Gizmo is 2 years old. She was kennelled alone at the shelter so we don’t yet know how she does with other dogs but she sure does love to play with people! We would love to find her a foster without other pets until we know for sure she is dog friendly. DM if you’d like more info on fostering!

I am heartbroken to say we lost our Pablo last night. I know so many of you have followed his story since 2018 when I first began fostering him then quickly realized he had always been meant for @christophervonsteinbach and I. Watching him transform from a dog that we joke had bitten half of the county of Los Angeles (and maybe a finger or two in Canada as well) to a dog that was pure love, trust and warmth was one of the greatest joys of my life. He was a testament that, with love and patience, we all have the ability to move forward towards better things. He inspired me to rescue 225 dogs and cats (so far) through @pacificpupsrescue. Thank you to everyone who knew and loved him and an extra special thank you to @kiahny2la, @azulmarin22 and @pacificpupsrescue for quite literally saving his life so that he could bless mine. ❤️

Happy holidays! 🎄

2023 was a year filled with plenty of personal and professional losses but also lots of wins and new beginnings. I got to travel, pose for beautiful photos, rescue more dogs, grow my side business, make new friends, spend time with family, and learn to live in that weird liminal space between two eras of your life.

This image of me taken back in the day for issue 1 of Missy Ink magazine has become one of the most widespread images of me ever taken. This photo keeps having new life breathed into it, from being tattooed on at least three strangers’ bodies to now discovering it is paste-up street art and murals in cities across Europe, the US and Chile by @palomarodriguez.cl! If you spot me in your city, send me a photo! 🎨
We’ve officially reached the Larry David statute of limitations on wishing people a happy New Year so don’t even think about it.
